### App Initialization

    > npm create vite@latest ./ -- --template react # --- Creates react template ---

### Install TailWIND CSS

    > npm install -D tailwindcss

    > npx tailwindcss init

### Remaining packages to install

    > npm install --legacy-peer-deps @react-three/fiber @react-three/drei maath react-tilt react-vertical-timeline-component @emailjs/browser framer-motion react-router-dom

##### 1. @react-three/fiber # --- Purpose: A React renderer for Three.js, a popular JavaScript library for 3D graphics.

##### 2. @react-three/drei # --- A utility library that provides helpers, abstractions, and reusable components for @react-three/fiber.

##### 3. maath # --- A mathematics and utilities library often used with @react-three/fiber to handle vectors, transforms, and other 3D math operations.

##### 4. react-tilt # --- A React wrapper for creating tilt or parallax effects on UI components.

##### 5. react-vertical-timeline-component # --- A React component for creating vertical timelines.

##### 6. @emailjs/browser # --- A library for sending emails directly from client-side JavaScript using EmailJS.

##### 7. framer-motion # --- a popular animation library for React

##### 8. react-router-dom # --- Provides routing capabilities for React apps.

### COMPONENTS

    - consists of empty structure for the project

### In order to use Tailwind CSS in Vite use below command

    - npm install --legacy-peer-deps -D postcss autoprefixer
    - npx tailwindcss init -p  #! --- creates config file for tailewind and postcss
